## PART 1 — PERMISSION SYSTEM

This is the foundation everything else builds on.
Every external API call that costs money goes through this gate.

### 1.1 Permission config (stored in project settings)

```ts
interface APIPermissions {
  // Per-API auto-approval settings
  heygen: PermissionConfig
  veo3: PermissionConfig
  imageGen: PermissionConfig
  backgroundRemoval: PermissionConfig
  elevenLabs: PermissionConfig
  unsplash: PermissionConfig     // free, but still trackable
}

interface PermissionConfig {
  mode: 'always_ask'    // ask every time (default)
        | 'always_allow' // never ask, just do it
        | 'always_deny'  // block completely, agent can't use this API
        | 'ask_once'     // ask first time per session, remember answer
  
  // Spend limits (optional)
  sessionLimit: number | null   // max $ to spend this session, null = unlimited
  monthlyLimit: number | null   // max $ this calendar month
  
  // Tracking
  sessionSpend: number          // running total this session
  monthlySpend: number          // running total this month
}
```

Default for all APIs: mode = 'always_ask', no limits.

### 1.2 Permission request flow

When the agent wants to call a paid API, it emits a special
tool call: request_permission(api, estimatedCost, reason).

This does NOT call the API. It pauses and sends a SSE event
to the frontend:

```ts
// SSE event type
{
  type: 'permission_request',
  id: string,              // unique request id
  api: string,             // 'heygen' | 'veo3' | 'imageGen' etc
  estimatedCost: string,   // '$0.08' | '$1.20' | 'unknown'
  reason: string,          // agent's explanation: "Generating avatar for intro scene"
  details: {               // what will be generated
    prompt?: string
    duration?: number
    model?: string
    resolution?: string
  }
}
```

Frontend shows a permission dialog in the chat panel:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ 🔑 Agent requesting API access                  │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ API:      HeyGen Avatar Generation              │
│ Reason:   Generate a presenter avatar for the  │
│           intro scene speaking the script       │
│ Cost:     ~$0.12 (12 credits)                  │
│ Prompt:   "Professional male presenter,         │
│           blue shirt, neutral background"       │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ [Allow once] [Always allow HeyGen] [Deny]       │
│ □ Don't ask again this session                  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

User response sends back:
```ts
{
  type: 'permission_response',
  id: string,
  decision: 'allow' | 'deny',
  remember: 'once' | 'session' | 'always'
}
```

Agent resumes only after receiving permission_response.
If denied: agent responds in chat explaining it can't proceed
and suggests alternatives.

### 1.3 Permission tool definition

```ts
// Tool the agent calls to request permission
{
  name: 'request_permission',
  description: `ALWAYS call this before calling any external 
  paid API including heygen_generate_avatar, veo3_generate_video,
  generate_image, remove_background, elevenlabs_tts.
  Wait for permission before proceeding.
  If permission mode is always_allow, this resolves immediately.
  If permission mode is always_deny, do not call the API.`,
  input_schema: {
    api: 'string — api identifier',
    estimatedCost: 'string — human readable cost estimate',
    reason: 'string — why you need this API for the user\'s request',
    details: 'object — what will be generated (prompt, duration, model etc)'
  }
}
```

### 1.4 Auto-approval handling

If PermissionConfig.mode === 'always_allow':
  request_permission resolves immediately with { decision: 'allow' }
  No UI dialog shown
  Agent continues without pause

If mode === 'always_deny':
  request_permission resolves with { decision: 'deny' }
  Agent receives denial, does not call the API
  Agent tells user this API is disabled and offers alternatives

If mode === 'ask_once' and already approved this session:
  resolves immediately with { decision: 'allow' }

