## PART 2 — HEYGEN AVATAR LAYER

### 2.1 What it is

HeyGen generates talking head videos from:
- A script (text or SSML)
- An avatar selection (from HeyGen's library or custom)
- Optional: voice selection

The result is an MP4 video with the avatar speaking.
We remove the background using BRIA RMBG to make it transparent.
Result: a WebM with alpha channel — the avatar floats over content.

### 2.2 Layer type

```ts
interface AvatarLayer extends BaseLayer {
  type: 'avatar'
  
  // HeyGen config
  avatarId: string          // HeyGen avatar ID
  voiceId: string           // HeyGen voice ID
  script: string            // what the avatar says
  
  // Background removal
  removeBackground: boolean // default true
  
  // Positioning on canvas
  x: number                 // center x (0-1920)
  y: number                 // center y (0-1080)
  width: number             // px
  height: number            // px
  
  // Result
  videoUrl: string | null   // URL to generated WebM with alpha
  thumbnailUrl: string | null
  
  // Generation state
  status: 'pending' | 'generating' | 'ready' | 'error'
  heygenVideoId: string | null  // for polling
  estimatedDuration: number     // seconds (from script length)
}
```

### 2.3 HeyGen API integration

```ts
