## PART 6 — BACKEND SETUP

### 6.1 New API routes

```
POST /api/generate-avatar
  Body: { sceneId, layerId, avatarConfig }
  Starts HeyGen job, returns { jobId }
  Polls in background, emits SSE when done

POST /api/generate-video
  Body: { sceneId, layerId, veo3Config }
  Starts Veo 3 job, returns { operationName }
  Polls in background, emits SSE when done

POST /api/generate-image
  Body: { sceneId, layerId?, imageConfig }
  Synchronous for fast models, returns { imageUrl }
  For stickers: also runs bg removal before returning

POST /api/remove-background
  Body: { imageUrl | imagePath }
  Runs BRIA RMBG, returns { resultUrl }

GET /api/list-avatars
  Returns cached HeyGen avatar list (refresh every 24h)
```

### 6.2 Media cache

All generated media cached locally to avoid re-generation:

```
/public/generated/
  avatars/{hash}.webm       # avatar videos with alpha
  videos/{hash}.mp4         # Veo 3 clips
  images/{hash}.png         # generated images
  stickers/{hash}.png       # bg-removed images
```

Cache key: hash of generation params (prompt + model + config).
Same prompt = same cache key = no re-generation cost.

