## CRITICAL NOTES

Permission gate is non-optional. If you implement any media
generation tool call WITHOUT first routing through
request_permission(), that is a bug. Every external paid API
call in the system goes through the gate. No exceptions.

WVC export with avatars: WebM with alpha plays correctly
in headless Chrome. WVC captures the composited frame
including the transparent avatar over other layers.
Test this in WVC before shipping.

Veo 3 availability: as of March 2026, Veo 3 is available
via Google AI Studio API key with waitlist access.
Add a graceful fallback: if Veo 3 returns 403/429,
tell the user and suggest Veo 2 or a Canvas2D animation instead.

Frame-by-frame avatar bg removal is compute-intensive.
Run on the render server (port 3001), not the Next.js server.
Cache aggressively — same avatar + same script = same video.

HeyGen green screen option: HeyGen supports generating avatars
on a pure green background natively, which is easier to chroma-key
than BRIA's neural approach. Test both and pick the cleaner result.
For hair and complex edges: BRIA wins.
For simple/clean studio avatars: green screen chroma-key via FFmpeg.

Sticker style guide for agent: always use `illustration` or `flat`
style for stickers, never `photorealistic`. Photo-realistic images
look bad after background removal due to edge artifacts.
Illustrations have clean, well-defined edges that remove cleanly.

Image cache deduplication: before calling any generation API,
check if a cached result exists for the same prompt+model+config hash.
If yes, return cached URL immediately. No API call, no cost, instant.
